      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Emgage Foundation demonstrates a robust commitment to financial health and transparency. With <cite id=\"5\">$4,918,661 in annual revenue</cite>, the organization has achieved a <cite id=\"12\">3-year revenue CAGR of 65.6%</cite>, indicating rapid growth and increasing donor trust. Their governance is supported by an <cite id=\"13\">independent board of directors</cite>, ensuring oversight and accountability. Furthermore, the organization is a significant grantmaker, distributing <cite id=\"14\">$920,000 in domestic grants</cite> to 33 recipients to support broader civic engagement ecosystems."
      ],
      "summary": "Emgage Foundation is a national, non-partisan organization that <cite id=\"1\">informs and mobilizes Muslim American voters</cite> to support policies that empower their communities. founded in 2017, the organization focuses on <cite id=\"2\">increasing political participation and systemic representation</cite> through a variety of civic engagement programs. Their flagship initiatives include the <cite id=\"3\">Million Muslim Votes Campaign</cite> and the <cite id=\"4\">Muslim Civic Table</cite>, which aim to build long-term political infrastructure. The foundation operates with a high degree of financial efficiency, reporting <cite id=\"5\">$4,918,661 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 tax year. Remarkably, the organization maintains a <cite id=\"6\">93.3% program expense ratio</cite>, ensuring that all funds are directed toward its core mission of civic empowerment. This lean operational model is further evidenced by its fundraising efficiency, as it spends only <cite id=\"7\">$0.01 to raise every $1 in contributions</cite>. By focusing on systemic change rather than direct aid, Emgage seeks to create a sustainable environment where Muslim Americans can <cite id=\"8\">forge a path to sustainable peace, freedom, and safety</cite> through the democratic process.",
